The paper is primarily concerned with the study of the succinctness of logics on linear orders, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also involves the comparison of different fragments of first-order logic, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of polynomial and exponential factors in the analysis suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of the expressiveness of different logics and their succinctness is also relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI).
